They had cute little bags to put your mask in and had a QR code for their menu on it though they still had paper menus they’d give out.  Also it was funny that it was about 7 degrees out so they had a heater near the door pointed into the restaurant to keep the draftiness down and one patron decided she wanted the heater only on her so everyone else got bursts of arctic air which provided another topic of conversation, thanks lady!

Unfortunately we were seated next to an open door Saturday night in 42° weather. After complaining and leaving the restaraunt, my personal information (from Open Table)  was shared with a former employee named Christopher Lee by either the manager on duty named Jennifer, or the waitress with the curly blonde hair and I was trolled on facebook within 2 hours of leaving, then blocked after I responded.  This is unacceptable.  In addition, my attempts to reach someone in regards to this personal breech of information has been ignored. So I then attempted.to contact upper management and found Suzi Craft had made a comment on the main facebook page. So I sent her a private message to please call me. Instead, she.chose to block me. They are also deleting my reviews on their facebook page. So, now i am.choosing to go public with this. Its not so much about the bad experience it happens and its water under the bridge,  its absolutely about the fact that they shared my full name to a employee Christopher Lee who then contacts me.on facebook under false pretense. There was absolutely no reason for this at all.

Going to a Brasserie at least couple of times a month. The food is so close to european and very tasty! My favorite is braised beef. I love that they have both menu items that are not changing and new options every couple of month. I recommend it for nice and classy date or evening!

I had just the best time at Brasserie by Niche tonight. I was a solo diner walking in at 9pm as I am just in the area for work briefly. The staff was so nice and accommodating and I really enjoyed the typical French, romantic atmosphere--it did  remind me of being back in Paris. I had the Goat Cheese Tart and the Beef tartare -- both were delicious and a generous portion. For dessert I had the Floating Island with an Americano (big points for having an espresso machine on hand!). Cocktails I tried were the Parisian, a perfect aperitif and the Brasserie Old Fashioned which was a nice twist on a classic. I honestly felt like the prices were on the cheaper side for what I was getting. Definitely  a great value. Gina was my server and did a wonderful job and although I didn't catch the manager's name, she was on point. I will definitely be back and bring my husband along next time. This is the perfect spot for date night--even if it's just yourself!

Even for a romantic dinner, my husband and I got a little impatient. There was also water dripping from above onto our table and food - likely condensation from the pipe - which detracted from the experience. We'll try going back another time to see if we just caught the kitchen on a busy/understaffed night.

Brasserie was an exceptional experience in a town filled with good food choices. I got an iron-skillet roast/seared chicken dish that was absolutely amazing and will definitely order again in the future. Their complementary bread is addictive, and their bacon salad is sublime. The staff here was very good and did an excellent job making sure our dining experience was one to remember. I just got home from Brasserie and wanted to write a review while I’m still floating from the wonderful experience! I had the bistro steak, French onion soup and floating island for dessert. My mom has the roasted chicken. It was all perfect! The service was excellent! Our server, Caleb, was personable and attentive. The manager, Jen also made sure that we were having a good experience and made the environment even more welcoming. The atmosphere is cozy, and the space is all around beautiful. Don’t wait for a special occasion, just go.

Delicious brunch with generous portions, loads of charm, and impeccably attentive service, Brassiere covers all the bases. You may find challenges with parking on the street, so be sure to use the available valet services.
Really really tasty! But I wouldn't recommend to most people most of the time.

From a server unable to give a recommendation, to cold coffee, to at best ok food with no one asking how it was and not being able to ask for condiments, no coffee refill and at last waiting for 15+ minutes after finishing the meal while sitting in front of an empty coffee cup to get the check the only thing I was happy about is that a week earlier we went some place else for Easter brunch.  Follow up, is that the only negative reviews this business responds to are those containing no text.  My family spends over 100k per year in restaurants around St Louis area and I assure you, not a penny was or will ever be spent in any restaurant associated with this place.

I was visiting town on business and our client recommended we grab drinks next door at Taste and have dinner at Brasserie.  What's the rule at restaurants?  Never order the chicken? I've been here for weekend brunch and for New Year's Eve. The staff are impeccable, the menu is quite French and a nice indulgent change of pace, and the food preparation is a bit hit-or-miss, in my limited experience.  I remember brunch being quite good, but it's been a while. On NYE (they may have been overwhelmed) the braised beef was in an overpoweringly salty sauce, the trout was a bit underwhelming, the mousse was ok with a rather bitter biscuit in it. The bread, sourced from a local bakery, was fantastic. Crowding can be an issue, it's so popular. If people don't clear out after eating it can interfere with later  reservations.

This was my first experience with this restaurant and I was very impressed. I went with a couple friends and a friend's family for dinner.  First, the wait time for food is longer than one would expected. If you are in a rush this is not the place to go. It is quite dim and comfortable.  However, the wait is worth it.  The food was extremely fresh and tasted amazing. The server was very kind, professional, and encouraged us to take our time.  There is not a parking structure but street parking is available. Outside looks very charming but can be easily missed. Overall, I had a great experience.

The meal was good.  The burger was above average and the trout was spectacular.  The wine and beer draft selection was welcome. The worst part of the experience was the cocktails, which is odd given the owners.  The cocktails were not properly balanced and with the normal “restaurant ice” added, it was a diluted muddled practically undrinkable experience.  We left our table after dinner and went to the bar for a different experience and upon inquiry for the rye used in the Sazarec, I was told dewar’s....I don’t even know how to respond to that.  I would contemplate going back because the food, ambience and service were good but just avoid the cocktail list entirely.

excellent good and service

High-class, high-quality, without a morsel of pretentiousness; it's both a step backward and a step forward into time, backward in that the ambiance reminds you of a scene in a Hollywood-glamour romance film, and forward when we inevitably as a species become less fascinated with our phones and seek something authentic; a bite of anything is less of what it is if our mind is elsewhere and that's the beauty of Brasserie: it draws you into the moment on its sheer charm alone, and fully present, you not only taste each bite, you feel it.  It's a truly special restaurant, and my favorite for good reason. I tend to go alone, but when I don't, I only bring very close friends, and enjoy watching their eyes light up when they sample any of the breathtaking items on the menu. The short answer: go to Brasserie.

My girlfriend and I went here for our anniversary, it was a nice quiet Sunday night in the Central West End. We sat inside and were promptly served drinks.  First of all I love the beer selection, it had plenty of different types of beers and some I've never heard of so I tried the Civil Life The Angel and the Sword (I love all things Civil Life), and the Octoberfest.  For Starter we ordered the Fromage which is a tray of various breads and cheeses. I've never had tasted anything quite like the cheese, but it tasted very rich and tangy, we loved the unique flavors.  For mains, my girlfriend had ordered the Scallop dish that came with potatoes and I ordered the Steak with fries plus an order of Mac and Cheese.  All of the dishes were amazing but the Mac and Cheese knocked my socks off. wow.  The steak was perfectly cooked medium rare and her scallops were top notch.  We loved our experience here.  It was a perfect way to celebrate our anniversary. Thank you Brasserie!

The menu had a lot of options & the food was excellent -- as was the service.  My wine-by-the-glass was a red blend that had a silken mouth feel and was absolutely delicious (Grenache-Mourvèdre-Syrah).  My daughter had the grapefruit mocktail and it was quite good as well. Lovely outdoor seating area in nice weather.   Unfortunately the food was sub-par.   Upon the recommendation of the server, we had the braised beef and roasted chicken.  Both meals were significantly over cooked and dried out.   The sauce on both dishes was extremely salty.  It’s possible the meals sat under the food warmer for too long as the servers appeared to be stretched pretty thin which impacted their attentiveness. I live in the CWE, and this restaurant is hands-down the best, most consistent, most delicious place to dine in the neighborhood. Every. Single. Time.  Last night we began with the frisée salad, which was beautifully presented with a perfectly cooked poached egg atop. I had the sea scallops, which were also cooked to perfection and paired with citrus and shallots - magnificent. My hubs had his go-to: the chicken, which is arguably the best chicken dish you will ever have. We had the chocolate mousse (with the house’s compliments) and a scoop of homemade ice cream for dessert. Magical from start to finish!  What separates Brasserie from the rest is the service that the team delivers. Jennifer, the GM, treats us like family every time we come in. Melinda, the bar GM, is equally warm, hospitable, and a lot of fun to converse with when we are at the bar with her. The waiters and waitresses take pride in the work they do, and they operate as one unified team - an indicator of great leadership at the helm.  Go to Brasserie, and you will never be disappointed!

Classy place but you dont feel you have to dress the part. Food is spectacular everything sampled was top notch. Def a brunch place. Have morning cocktails. I prefer my French toast on the crispy crunch side but this is not it. But still well done taste. But the whipped lemon curd pushed this to the top not even needing syrup.) French breakfast- looks like cheese board but was told very good (7 of 10)Brisket tartine (10 of 10 if they could make this better I do not know how. My wife was extremely happy and the deserts were very good as well. Nice bourbon and wine selection and the service was incredibly attentive and friendly.   We will certainly go back again.

Delicious and our server was super awesome!

OMD! (That's "Oh Mon Dieu!" 😍) As anyone who has read my reviews knows, I don't hand out 5 Stars very often; you really have to blow me away to get 5.  Well, Gerard Kraft's Brasserie by Niche deserves 6 stars! Kraft is an award-winning chef and has created other outstanding restaurants in the St. Louis area, so it should surprise no one that his new Brasserie continues the trend. But Brasserie by Niche is not just "echt" French cuisine; they have captured the ambience and the attitude as well. If you have dined in Paris brasseries in the past, you'll probably be snobby and say this isn't quite authentic. But from fresh patés, smooth gratinée (soupe à l'oignon) and fresh locally sourced meats, vegetables and cheeses, Brasserie is the best St. Louis/French cooking on this side of the Atlantic. Wines are great too--nothing out of reach, but still top-notch reds and whites. Didn't have room for dessert (next time), but the mousse au chocolat and the profitéroles looked beautiful. All in all, a stellar meal.

This was my first experience with this restaurant and I was very impressed. I went with a couple of friends and a friend's family for dinner. First, the wait time for food is longer than one would expected. If you are in a rush this is not the place to go. It is quite dim and comfortable. However, the wait is worth it. The food was extremely fresh and tasted amazing. The server was very kind, professional, and encouraged us to take our time. There is not a parking structure but street parking is available. Outside looks very charming but can be easily missed. Overall, I had a great experience.

Really nice atmosphere.  Not upscale nice.  Just a different experience.  I went based on a recommendation from my stylist.  I was not impressed.  Tables are way to close.  I didn't go to network with the people next to me.  Which happen to be 5 inches away.  Kind of expensive.  I had the dish with white beans, sausage and rice.  And it had a big hunk of salt pork on the side.  You should try it.  It is a once every six month place for me.
I would love to eat there
The food is fine but does not match up to its cost. The drinks are small and the crowd is a better dressed version from the Olive Garden.

This is one of my favorite restaurants in the city. It is special without being too formal or over-priced. Wonderful food and drinks-- I would especially recommend the braised beef. And the mousse is amazing. We came here for my husband's birthday and we will absolutely be back often.
The steak was delicious and tender.
Always great food for a reasonable price. Classic “farmhouse” French food like cassoulet and what is one of the best roast chickens in town. A go-to dinning spot for me.
Lovely restaurant with amazing menu! It was our anniversary and the whole staff was amazing. Our waiter, Caleb, was very attentive! Thank you for making our evening so special!
Arguably the best restaurant in town. Perfect Frisee Salad. Delicious French Onion Soup. Mouthwatering Shoestring Fries and perfectly cooked steak.

Upscale french restaurant with an excellent menu of countryside favorites and chique presentation. The wine and liquor menu is solid with a fairly large number of great whiskies at a reasonable price. I definitely recommend the pork belly and braised beef, but everyone in my party enjoyed it. The restaurant is busy even on a Tuesday, so reservations are advised.
Great food and service!
Fantastic food and atmosphere. Highly recommended.
Really enjoyed our meal.  A bit loud and close to other tables so have to focus to hear your part not others.  But food was great.
Food was ok, service mediocre, place cold
I had a wonderful experience here. The food was amazing and the staff was very friendly and accommodating. It's a tad bit expensive, but totally worth it as I will remember that meal my whole life.
Favourite dinner place.
A bit disappointing, normally exquisite, poached eggs on bennie overdone, missed the eng muffin all about the classic texture...
Great atmosphere little over priced
Great food and atmosphere. The fries are the best I’ve had in STL!
My husband & I had a great experience! We ate at the bar before our show at the Fox and we were on a time crunch. The bartenders were both so accommodating and the food was excellent.
I love this place, the food is amazing and the service is just as great.
Best French food I've had in the States. Was as good as Daniel and Denise in Lyon.
Good food kitchen clean
Great food!!

Great place to get familiar with basic home cooked French food. The prices are a bit higher than the ingredients would warrant, must be the function of supply (few French restaurants) and demand (public interest for French food).
High quality food but nothing ground breaking.
Good food. Good wine. Good price. Superior ambiance.  But, loud when crowded.
Always awesome!

Nice restaurant  in the  central west end. We had a party of five with reservations all arriving 5 to10 minutes apart.  We came for brunch with the restaurant  being crowded and were seated immediately.  Beignets and coffee  were ordered and served very quickly.  Everyone ordered something different for an entree  and everyone loved their choice.  I would recommend Brasserie by Niche and will return.
Awesome food and attentive service
Fantastic service, wonderful food! Simple ingredients combined into delicious dishes. Elegant feel without being stuffy.
I had a beautiful vegetable tart; my companions had a braised beef dish which was also very good.

Very pricy for what it is. The escargot are watery (you want the butter to be thick enough so that it actually comes with the escargot when you pick one). The "steak frites béarnaise" is really a half pound of fries and the sauce falls quite short of being anything close to a bearnaise. Overall it was also very salty. Oh and when you order a $12 glass of wine, you'd want it served from the bottle in front of you - at least that's what you'd expect from a place that calls itself an old fashion brasserie. I would know, I'm from France.
Enjoyed the outdoor dining area on a warm October night. The menu du jour was delicious with thoughtfully paired dishes. Friendly service.
Great service and ambiance
Amazing the second time too!
(Translated by Google) Delicious and professional  (Original) Délicieux et professionnels
Fine Dining in and out doors in a  comfortable setting relaxed atmosphere.
Easy valet, friendly staff, best french soup
Nice happy hour special and a great place to sit outside and people watch.
Incredible brunch! Real French butter on EVERYTHING
Waffle with blueberrys is awesome for brunch.
Food was good for brunch... Could have had similar fair in many other places... Service was slow for how not too busy it was... Left hungry.
Wonderful menu and fantastic staff. One of the crown jewels of the CWE!
Great service, great food
Best happy hour!
Best brunch in town!
Amazing food, don’t get the French breakfast, that’s easily the worst thing on the menu. The French breakfast isn’t bad, it’s just very simple
Delicious food, very well prepared. Ate on the patio as the weather was perfect. Pricey but really good.

Great atmosphere, great service, but the food leaves something to be desired.  It's decent, but for the highest rated restaurant in the area I was expecting much better.  The food is a bit too buttery and I think the menu could be more interesting, especially for a "French" restaurant. It seems very "wannabe nice restaurant" and if you've been to good restaurant in NYC, Chicago or even Cleveland you'll be disappointed.  Most people won't notice this, and maybe I got unlucky, but the dishes had a terrible smell.  The glasses, the utensils and the plates all had this smell.  I noticed this it during he meal but figured it was something in the air until I got a good wiff of the silverware during dessert, so if you've got a sensitive noise I would be wary of this place.  P.S.  I had dinner.
A bit overpriced, but they gave us free champagne because we had to wait for a table even though we had a reservation. The roast chicken and French onion soup were delicious!

I think this may very well be the best meal I've ever had.  The Brioche French Toast quite literally has changed my life.  Our server Sarah was very attentive and did a great job.  My only complaint is it was approximately a 45 minute wait between ordering and our food arriving.

Wow! Incredible! My wife and I went out to celebrate Belgian National Day (Bon Fête Nationale!) and were seeking something befitting of the cuisine of her home. Brasserie was the perfect fit! Our service was beyond great! The food was perfect! The atmosphere is exactly what you’d expect if you strolled into a Brasserie in Brussels, or Paris. I highly recommend this place for a nice evening out. Price is $$ (on a $ - $$ - $$$ scale). Very much worth it.

Best customer service I’ve had in St. Louis in a very long time! Food was absolutely delicious! Server made a minor mistake with my order and the went way above and beyond to make up for it! Would highly recommend eating here!
Wonderful brunch!  Different than others, but delicious. Try the Beignets! The cream cheese and plums that accompany is truly fabulous.
Very delicious and a great happy hour.

we went for my birthday. We were able to sit outside, and the wait staff was very accommodating. It was my 35th birthday, and they provided us dessert with a cute candle and a message from the chef. It was very thoughtful. We ordered the brisket and it was so incredible. We would have gotten more if there was an option to!
This restaurant is wonderful, the service is excellent. There is a great selection of wine to choose from, and last but not least the food is awesome!
Exceptional food, wonderful atmosphere and our new favorite place to meet and eat.
One of the simplest and best happy hours to be had in the city. Same could be said of the cheeseburger.
Fun atmosphere, real French food and delicious cheese board
Wonderful.  Satisfies my love for French cuisine.
Wow... This place blew my mind. Every dish was executed perfectly. My  favorite Bistro
Simple menu but good food.

Went to Brasserie this past Saturday and had a really enjoyable experience. Had a full meal at the bar and Lindsey took great care of us. The escargot, trout amandine, and baked alaska were fantastic. Will definitely be back.
Nice ambience but over priced.

LOVE this place! The food is fresh, elegant and well-prepared. Whenever I'm in STL, I make sure to stop by -- and pray that the Coq au Vin is on the menu. Even if it's not, though, you can't go wrong.
Love this place.
Exquisite atmosphere, delicious food!
Had a great time with great food and atmosphere.
Went here for a business dinner and thoroughly enjoyed the food here. Without a doubt the onion soup is hands down the best French onion style soup I’ve ever had anywhere in the world.

My favorite brunch spot in the CWE!  Mimosas have fresh squeezed OJ.  There not a single thing on the menu I wouldn't recommend but my favorite is the eggs Benedict! Sit at the bar too... Chris will keep you entertained!
Staff, food and drinks were outstanding.  I cannot wait to return!
Great place for a nice dinner date

Justin was a fantastic manager who insured we had a very special evening.  Waiter Alexa was supurb.  She went out of her way to help.  Thanks a million for alk you do. Cauliflower Soup, Chicken, and molten chocolate cake were to die for. Thanks.  I promise i will never visit St. Louis again without coming in for a wonderful eating experience!  Glenn
The food was delicious and dessert was divine. Casual atmosphere and lively.
Great food, great service. Braised beef is amazing. Drinks are on point!
Great food and service. The Niche family of restaurants are always great.
It waa okay, I found nothing spectacular or that I just had to have.
Fabulous, as always!
REALLY nice experience! Everything was top notch. I highly recommend...
FAVORITE BRUNCH. My wife and I love it, and the food and staff is always amazing. Great cocktails too.
Incredible dishes. I have loved everything I have eaten here from the salad course to dessert. A bit on the pricey side, but worth every penny.
Great food
Wonderful food and $7 Classic Cocktails all evening (Sunday & Monday) - what a deal!
Fantastic food and wine. Somehow the food seems so fancy when ordering but it's simple ingredients yet amazing taste are wonderfully confusing
Been here a couple times and the food has been really good.

Was hoping for a little quieter spot, but that's ok. Otherwise the food was amazing. The braised beef is super tender and full of flavor. My folks had the trout, and while I'm not generally a big fan of fish, it was really tasty as well. My girlfriend had the veggie tart, she really liked it, but not my style. Creme brulee for dessert was also excellent.

I adore here. I normally don’t eat meat but all their options are incredibly flavorful. Their team is friendly and make sure we are well attended. Is cozy and has that sophisticated French flare. Their menu is not huge but for me every time I went was amazing. I ordered the rosbife sandwich. Their fries are addictive. The bread is cute and the chocolate mousse is a splurge.
wonderful New Year's brunch

The food here is fantastic! Our server tonight was Max. He has only worked there for two weeks, but he took care of multiple tables flawlessly. Also, you have to try the lardons! Had them on my salad and got a side order with my steak. Love this place!
Prompt, attentive service.  Excellent brunch. Best burger in stl.
Fantastic food and a cozy atmosphere
Midwest imitation of a brasserie. Successful along one dimension: the noise.
Highly recommend. Great beignets, awesome service.
I love their lunch & dinner

If you want to get your brunch on, look no further. This french style cuisine is pretty bomb. I tried the french toast with lemon custard. I didn't even know I was obsessed with lemon custard but I definitely am now.  My partner had a breakfast like skillet which was savory and filling. There were so many nuances like plush bench seats to small creamer holders. The staff seem to really enjoy working where they do which is always comforting.  Now, this is not some where I could afford as student to numerous mimosas or turn up on a Sunday. The price range is higher but its worth it because of the quality. However, if you want a lovely breakfast with a SO or friends, I would highly recommend checking this out. Also, the patio is dog friendly, bonus!

Went for brunch and it was fantastic! All four of us had great meals and drinks and it was all the perfect portion size. Call ahead though, cause even though they have a lot of room, everyone else is trying to get in too!

Had a great experience here during lunch a few weeks back.  Finally getting around to writing a review!  There were four of us in our business group and everyone ordered something different.  We were all very happy with the food and service.  Give the Brasserie a try!  It's a little on the pricey side but the food is very good.

I took a group here for dinner and the food was phenomenal.  I had the trout and we shared a meat and cheese platter.  It was more than enough food to leave our party of 6 feeling well fed.  We took advantage of their happy hour by arriving early and enjoyed half off beer and wine during our meal (4-7)
Always wonderful to return here.  Superb service, great menu options plus lovely ambiance.
Is ok. Not great not bad... Great service and drinks. Food is ok
Friendly staff.  We had the menu of the day and everything was excellent.  Try the pumpkin soup.  Yummy

The menu selection was very limited specially if you don't eat red meat. The food was tasty a little too salty for me but my companion didn't agree. Staff was very nice. Unless I'm with someone who really wants to go here I doubt I'd go again
Good burgers. Great bread!
Great food and atmosphere. One of my favorite places to go in St Louis!
Great food and service, indoor or outdoor dining
